			<translation>
				The Three Books of old and Recent Jokes, by Adriaan van Baerland,
				taken from Macrobius, Quintilian, Cicero, Suetonius, Diogenes Laertius, Plutarch, Giovanni Pontano,
				Erasmus, Martial, Horace, Ausonius, Thomas Moore.
				I am in the habit of adding Castiglione's Courtier, the Mensa Philosophica, Wilson's Rhetoric,
				the French source of joy, Rabelais, and Manlius. But there is nothing entirely comparable to the 
				Stratagems, either in utility or enjoyment. Skills, stratagems, pregnant jokes.
				Likewise, the many precautions of pragmatic men.
			</translation>
