		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="90">
					<marginalia_text>
						Vita Plinio vigilia: Seneca[e] militia. Quid Ca[e]sari? quid Hyperca[e]sari?
					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Pliny the Elder"/>
					<person name="Seneca"/>
					<person name="Julius Caesar"/>
					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				The vigilant life is found in Pliny, the militant life in Seneca. What of Caesar? What of Super-Cesar? 
						<!-- CG: Unclear of term 'Hypercaesar'. Specialist help appreciated! -->
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="right_margin" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						In rebus afflictis, Patie[n]tia[e] doctor Augustinus: securitatis, Epictetus: tranquilitatis,  
					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Augustine"/>
					<person name="Epictetus"/>
					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
				</position>
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						Seneca: serenitatis, Antoninus: iucunditatis, Vespasianus:
						la[e]titia[e], Julius, et 
						splendoris. 
						Nunq[uam]
						magnificentior, qu&agrave;m c&ugrave;m oppugnatus maxim&egrave;.
					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Seneca"/>
					<person name="Marcus Aurelius"/>
					<person name="Vespasian"/>
					<person name="Julius Caesar"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				In vexing situations, Augustine is the teacher of patience; Epictetus of safety; 
				Seneca of tranquility; Marcus Aurelius of serenity; Vespasian of pleasantness;
				Julius of fruitfulness and splendor. Never is Julius more magnificent than when he is
				under heavy attack.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						Nihil omnes Oratores, aut Philosophi, aut etiam historici, ad Julium.
					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Julius Caesar"/>
					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Compared to Julius, all Orators, Philosophers, and even Historians, are nothing.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
